Sentencas: Ba0.5Sr0.5FeO3-& delta; (BSF) nanofibers are prepared via electrospinning and sintering at a temperature of 800 & DEG;C for 2 h to produce a pure cubic perovskite phase, with the aim of finding a high-performance cathode material suitable for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (PCFCs) operating at medium temperatures.
Titulo: Application of Ba0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ-NdMnO3-δ Composite Cathode in Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results of SEM analysis showed that the BSF nanofibers are alternately stacked, presenting fluffy and uniform high porosity, which is favorable to the cathode polarization reaction of PCFCs.
Titulo: Application of Ba0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ-NdMnO3-δ Composite Cathode in Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: To balance the excessive coefficient of thermal expansion of the BSF cathode, it is combined with a negative thermal expansion (NTE) material NdMnO3-& delta; (NM).
Titulo: Application of Ba0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ-NdMnO3-δ Composite Cathode in Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: At 700 & DEG;C, the peak power density (PPD) of the BSF-NM cathode cell is 1170 mW cm(-2), and the open-circuit voltage (OCV) of the single cell is 1.04 V. The corresponding polarization impedance (R-p) of the BSF-NM is 0.037 & omega; cm(2).
Titulo: Application of Ba0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ-NdMnO3-δ Composite Cathode in Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This result is significantly better than the previously reported powder cathode BSF, indicating that the performance of PCFC can be further optimized by transforming the BSF cathode into a nanofiber state and compounding it with the NTE material NM.
Titulo: Application of Ba0.5Sr0.5FeO3-δ-NdMnO3-δ Composite Cathode in Proton-Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
